div.div:
When a new replica is added, clients first get updates of latest membership and they stop sending request until all replicas become ready.
Then other replicas get updates of membership. The primary replica first checks the real status of the new replica (which might be already READY) and then finishes processing all requests it receives and then gives the latest checkpoint to the new replica. This avoids any message lost due to lag between logging and processing.
